# Exo:
During the migration process, the Nautilus DevOps team created several EC2 instances in different regions. 
They are currently in the process of identifying the correct resources and utilization and are making continuous changes to ensure optimal resource utilization. 
Recently, they discovered that one of the EC2 instances was underutilized, prompting them to decide to change the instance type. 
Please make sure the Status check is completed (if its still in Initializing state) before making any changes to the instance.

## Requirements:
1. Change the instance type from t2.micro to t2.nano for devops-ec2 instance.
2. Make sure the ec2 instance devops-ec2 is in running state after the change.

# Solution:
1- Open the Amazon EC2 Dashboard. Under Resource section, choose instances
2- Select `devops-ec2` instance and Stop it from Instance state dropdown menu.
3- After the instance statut changed to stopped:
  a- Click on Actions dropdown menu and choose Instance settings then Change instance type image
  b- Choose your new instance type from t2.micro to `t2.nano`
4- Start instance from Instance state dropdown menu and verify if it is `running` and the type is `t2.nano`
